  "response": "Here are some general tips for shopping Religion courses at Harvard College:\n\n1. Explore Course Catalog\n- Look through the course catalog carefully\n- Check course descriptions and syllabi\n- Review potential course topics and focus areas\n\n2. Consider Course Levels\n- Introductory courses (100-level)\n- Intermediate courses (200-level)\n- Advanced seminars (300-level)\n\n3. Faculty Research\n- Review professors' backgrounds\n- Check their research interests\n- Look at their published work\n- Consider their teaching style\n\n4. Course Requirements\n- Check reading load\n- Examine writing expectations\n- Review assessment methods\n- Understand participation requirements\n\n5. Distribution Requirements\n- See if courses fulfill general education requirements\n- Check if credits apply to specific concentrations\n\n6. Seek Recommendations\n- Talk to academic advisors\n- Consult students who have taken similar courses\n- Attend shopping week presentations\n\n7. Breadth and Depth\n- Consider courses covering different religious traditions\n- Look for comparative or interdisciplinary approaches\n- Balance theoretical and historical perspectives\n\n8. Time and Schedule\n- Check course meeting times\n- Consider workload alongside other courses\n\nRemember to attend initial class sessions during shopping week to get a better sense of each course.",
